    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-31T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/1578: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-31T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 31, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 54, March 29, 4 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d732fn2">Not printed.</note> You
                    may inform the Minister for Foreign Affairs: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>That the Convention for renewal of the General Claims Commission<note
                                n="3" xml:id="d732fn3">Signed June 18, 1932, <ref
                                    target="frus1932v05#pg_740">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                        rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 740</ref>.</note> does not
                            require prior advice and consent to ratification by the Senate of the
                            United States and may be brought into force at any time by exchange of
                            ratifications.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>That inasmuch as the protocol supplementing the Convention for renewal
                            of the Special Claims Commission<note n="4" xml:id="d732fn4">Signed June
                                18, 1932, <ref target="frus1932v05#pg_744">
                                    <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 744</ref>.</note> contains
                            subject matter deemed to be not within the purview of the original
                            Convention of September 10, 1923,<note n="5" xml:id="d732fn5">
                                <ref target="frus1923v02#pg_560">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                        >ii</hi>, p. 560</ref>.</note> that Convention has been
                            submitted to the Senate of the United States for its advice and consent
                            to ratification. The matter has been referred to the Senate Committee on
                            Foreign Relations and is still pending.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
